node.title: Stuart Highway to reopen to trucks and emergency vehicles
node.alt: Blue sky, bitumen highway under brown water, flooded
node.description: The Stuart Highway will reopen to trucks and emergency services vehicles at 7am tomorrow, restoring the main road link between South Australia and the Northern Territory.
node.content: ["The Stuart Highway will reopen to trucks and emergency services vehicles at 7am tomorrow, restoring the main road link between South Australia and the Northern Territory.", "The South Australian government says four-wheel drives and other high-clearance vehicles will be able to use the road from Tuesday.", "Initially, it will only be open to one vehicle at a time during daylight hours, travelling down the middle of the highway with a police escort.", "More than 1\u00a0metre of water has been slowly receding since heavy rains fell around Glendambo in South Australia's north more than a week ago.", "More to come."]
